questions.subject: ComfyUI-Inference-Core-Nodes
questions.question: What are the performance benchmarks for the ComfyUI-Inference-Core-Nodes?
questions.answer: The performance benchmarks include Milliseconds per Iteration, Iters per Second for each model, Time per operator type, and Feature Memory Read and Written per operator type.

questions.subject: EfficientNet-B0
questions.question: What are the differences in performance between the optimized and unoptimized version of the EfficientNet-B0 model in terms of Milliseconds per Iteration and Iters per Second?
questions.answer: The optimized version of the EfficientNet-B0 model has a Milliseconds per Iteration of 46.0838 and Iters per second of 21.6996, while the unoptimized version has a Milliseconds per Iteration of 49.2862 and Iters per second of 20.2897.

questions.subject: TF MobileNet-V3 Large 1.0
questions.question: What is the optimized Milliseconds per Iteration and Iters per Second for the TF MobileNet-V3 Large 1.0 model?
questions.answer: The optimized Milliseconds per Iteration for the TF MobileNet-V3 Large 1.0 model is 22.0495, and the Iters per Second is 45.3525.

questions.subject: MobileNet-V3 (RW)
questions.question: What are the Total FLOP per operator type for the optimized and unoptimized versions of the MobileNet-V3 (RW) model?
questions.answer: For the optimized version of the MobileNet-V3 (RW) model, the Total FLOP per operator type is 0.438542 GFLOP, and for the unoptimized version, it is 0.456141 GFLOP.

questions.subject: MnasNet-A1
questions.question: What are the differences in performance between the optimized and unoptimized version of the MnasNet-A1 model in terms of Milliseconds per Iteration and Time per operator type?
questions.answer: The optimized version of the MnasNet-A1 model has a Milliseconds per Iteration of 24.2367 and the Time per operator type is mostly attributed to Conv (91.1375%), while the unoptimized version has a Milliseconds per Iteration of 30.0892 and the Time per operator type is mostly attributed to Conv (79.0905%).

questions.subject: MnasNet-B1
questions.question: What are the differences in FLOP per operator type for the optimized and unoptimized versions of the MnasNet-B1 model?
questions.answer: The optimized version of the MnasNet-B1 model has a Total FLOP per operator type of 0.629124 GFLOP, while the unoptimized version has a Total FLOP per operator type of 0.650951 GFLOP.

questions.subject: ComfyUI-Inference-Core-Nodes
questions.question: Which model has the fastest Iters per second in the ComfyUI-Inference-Core-Nodes benchmark?
questions.answer: EfficientNet-B0 has the fastest Iters per second with 21.6996 optimized and 20.2897 unoptimized.
